        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 11:52PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 1152 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Centrahoma, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stuart, Lamar, and Gerty.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
